history.text: I really loved this movie.
Yes, it was very interesting.
Leonardo did great!
I wasn't aware of the story at first, but I really did like the tone and style it used to convey how silly and unbelievable the whole thing was.
Yes, it was indeed silly.
I know a lot of people didn't like it because they thought it was glorifying a criminal, but I thought that the main character didn't come across as likable at all. It was just entertaining.
I didn't mind him.
Did you think the story was accurate or did you think some parts where embellished?
I think that the story was definitely embellished but honestly it was entertaining and I would watch it again if I was asked to.
What was your favorite part? I think I liked the part where they were first getting the company started. It was great to see how an empire starts from humble beginnings.
Meh, not really. I prefer the scenes when Jordan got pissed. They're funny to me.
I actually liked the more technical aspects of the movie like how they started off by dealing penny stocks.
Yeah. Not me, I prefer the dialogue and character development more.
I thought the acting was good too. I didn't used to like Leo but as he's matured I think he's gotten better as an actor. Like you said, he was pretty good in this film.
I've always liked his movies, especially the well-known Titanic.
Do you think that Leo deserved an Oscar for Wolf Of Wallstreet?
Maybe, I'd say there's a lot of competition for him, even. So probably not.
Speaking of some more scenes I liked, I also liked the parts where he goes overseas to hide his money. Things like that are interesting to me.
Really? That's neat. I like drama so the affair with Jordan was really more interesting to me.
Which scenes that involved drama did you like?
When his wife found out, and when the FBI got way more involved.
Action scenes too.
I see. Yeah I did like the scenes that involved how his actions and personality started to affect his family.
Yeah, heart wrenching. I can't believe he tried running off with his daughter after the divorce.

Am I the only one who didn't like the character that Jonah Hill played. I mean the actor was good but the character was somebody I found despicable and I hated how he was mainly the reason the business was destroyed.
I mean probably not. I'm sure there's a majority vote corresponding to how you find his character to be despicable. I myself don't blame you for that. The business was ruined by Donnie.
But I guess at the end of the day, you can't be too mad that a criminal ruined his criminal buddy's business.
It happens.
I do think that as despicable as the characters were you have to admire their street smarts.
